South African writer Sisonke Msimang has moved to Australia with her family . 
  She said the 'deepest and most abiding forms of racism’ in Australia are directed toward our own indigenous population . 
  She has recognised a systematic approach to ‘assimilate’ and ‘eradicate’ Australia’s Indigenous heritage . 
  She slammed Prime Minister Tony Abbott for his 'out of touch' comments . 
  MsMsimang said Australia is more racist than her native South Africa where segregation by skin colour was the law . 
 